## Session Management

### Starting a Session
```bash
# Terminal
bash .kiro/hooks/session-start.sh

# Or with alias
kiro-start
```

**In Kiro** (copy-paste):
```
Please read .kiro/SESSION_INIT.md to load the full project context
```

### During Session (Every 30 min)
```bash
bash .kiro/hooks/session-checkpoint.sh

# Or with alias
save
```

### Saving Conversation
```bash
# Save conversation from temporary.md
bash .kiro/hooks/save-conversation.sh

# Or with alias
save-conv
```

### Updating Context
```bash
# Quick auto-update (non-interactive)
bash .kiro/hooks/auto-update.sh
# Or: auto-update

# Full interactive update (asks 4 questions)
bash .kiro/hooks/update-context.sh
# Or: update-context
```

### Ending Session
```bash
bash .kiro/hooks/session-end.sh

# Or with alias
kiro-end
```

### Complete End-of-Session Workflow
```bash
# 1. Save conversation
save-conv

# 2. Add semantic context
update-context

# 3. Checkpoint everything
save

# 4. End session
kiro-end
```

