## Task Completion Workflow

### 1. Find Next Task
```bash
cat .kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/tasks.md
# Or
grep "\[ \]" .kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/tasks.md | head -5
```

### 2. Understand the Task
```bash
# Check requirements
grep -A 10 "Requirement 1.1" .kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/requirements.md

# Check design
grep -A 10 "Maven" .kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/design.md
```

### 3. Implement the Task
- Write code
- Create files
- Configure systems
- Follow project standards

### 4. Test Implementation
```bash
# Backend
cd backend
mvn test

# Frontend
cd frontend
npm test
```

### 5. Mark Task Complete
```bash
bash .kiro/hooks/task-complete.sh 1.1.1
# Replace 1.1.1 with actual task number
```

### 6. Run Checkpoint
```bash
bash .kiro/hooks/session-checkpoint.sh
```

### Task Completion Checklist
- [ ] Task implementation complete
- [ ] Code follows project standards
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Code committed
- [ ] Documentation updated (if needed)
- [ ] No errors or warnings
- [ ] Acceptance criteria met

