## Useful Aliases

Add to `~/.zshrc` or `~/.bashrc`:

```bash
# Navigation
alias kiro='cd /Users/syedrahman/Desktop/Career-and-Growth/KIRO/interview-prep-attempt-100'

# Session Management
alias kiro-start='bash .kiro/hooks/session-start.sh'
alias kiro-end='bash .kiro/hooks/session-end.sh'
alias kiro-resume='bash .kiro/hooks/session-resume.sh'
alias save='bash .kiro/hooks/session-checkpoint.sh'
alias save-conv='bash .kiro/hooks/save-conversation.sh'
alias auto-update='bash .kiro/hooks/auto-update.sh'
alias update-context='bash .kiro/hooks/update-context.sh'

# Development
alias backend='cd backend && mvn spring-boot:run'
alias frontend='cd frontend && npm run dev'
alias build='cd backend && mvn clean package'

# Status
alias status='cat .kiro/session-state/current-phase.json'
alias tasks='grep "\[ \]" .kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/tasks.md | head -10'
alias progress='cat .kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/PROGRESS.md'
```

**Reload aliases**:
```bash
source ~/.zshrc
# or
source ~/.bashrc
```

