## Documentation Structure

### Core Spec Files (Single Source of Truth)
- `.kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/requirements.md` - WHAT to build
- `.kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/design.md` - HOW to build
- `.kiro/specs/comprehensive-learning-portal/tasks.md` - WHEN to build

### Context & Session Management
- `temporary.md` - Current session notes (active workspace)
- `.kiro/session-state/context-summary.md` - Consolidated full context
- `.kiro/session-state/resume-context.md` - Quick session overview
- `.kiro/session-logs/` - Archived session history

### Workflow Guides (All Auto-Loaded for Kiro)
- `.kiro/steering/CONTEXT_MANAGEMENT_GUIDE.md` - How to manage context
- `.kiro/steering/SPEC_DRIVEN_WORKFLOW.md` - Spec-driven development workflow
- `.kiro/steering/SESSION_GUIDE.md` - Complete session guide
- `.kiro/steering/KIRO_CHECKLIST.md` - Kiro's pre-flight checklist
- `.kiro/steering/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` - Coding standards and testing
- `.kiro/steering/PROJECT_STATUS.md` - Project progress tracking

### How to Use
**Starting a session**:
1. Read `PROGRESS.md` - See where you left off
2. Check `CHANGELOG.md` - Review recent changes
3. Open `tasks.md` - Find your next task

**During work**:
1. Update `PROGRESS.md` after each task
2. Mark tasks in `tasks.md`
3. Run `session-checkpoint.sh` regularly

**After completing work**:
1. Update `PROGRESS.md` with accomplishments
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md` for milestones
3. Run `session-end.sh`

